        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:18PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Morton, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Morton around 425 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
